{"title":"DirtySixer tease 36er AllRoad Mark II bike for the tallest riders (up to 7′ 6″)","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/11/01/dirty-sixer-tease-36er-all-road-mark-ii-bike-for-the-tallest-riders-up-to-7-6/","date":1635767302000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064813/SHAQ-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-INCH-WHEEL-ALL-ROAD-COMMUTER-BIKE.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"497\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064813/SHAQ-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-INCH-WHEEL-ALL-ROAD-COMMUTER-BIKE-800x497.jpg\" alt=\"SHAQ WANDA RIDING 36ER DIRTYSIXER ALL-ROAD COMMUTER BIKE VERY TALL PEOPLE\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064813/SHAQ-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-INCH-WHEEL-ALL-ROAD-COMMUTER-BIKE-800x497.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064813/SHAQ-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-INCH-WHEEL-ALL-ROAD-COMMUTER-BIKE-297x185.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064813/SHAQ-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-INCH-WHEEL-ALL-ROAD-COMMUTER-BIKE-120x75.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064813/SHAQ-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-INCH-WHEEL-ALL-ROAD-COMMUTER-BIKE-768x477.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064813/SHAQ-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-INCH-WHEEL-ALL-ROAD-COMMUTER-BIKE.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-276679\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>DirtySixer is updating their 36″ wheel AllRoad commuter bike for extra tall people through to extra, extra, extra, extra, extra tall people. Now Mark II, the 36er will shortly be available in sizes XL-5XL with a whopping pre-order discount of $2000 USD. Past customers of the DirtySixer AllRoad include LeBron James, Mark Eaton, Kevin Durant, and Shaquille O’Neal, spotted riding his DirtySixer AllRoad with Wanda Sykes in tow in an American Express Commercial.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064810/SHAQUILLE-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-ALL-ROAD-TV-ADD.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064810/SHAQUILLE-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-ALL-ROAD-TV-ADD.jpg\" alt=\"shaq towing wanda syker dirty sixer 36er commuter bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1034\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064810/SHAQUILLE-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-ALL-ROAD-TV-ADD.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064810/SHAQUILLE-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-ALL-ROAD-TV-ADD-297x256.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064810/SHAQUILLE-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-ALL-ROAD-TV-ADD-800x689.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064810/SHAQUILLE-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-ALL-ROAD-TV-ADD-120x103.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064810/SHAQUILLE-WANDA-DIRTYSIXER-36-ALL-ROAD-TV-ADD-768x662.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p><em>“I have got a lot of things done custom for me in my career, but nothing quite like that. I feel like a kid again! I’d like to order another one like that for my other house” –</em> Shaquille O’Neal, 7′ 1″.&nbsp;</p><h2>DirtySixer AllRoad MK2</h2><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/yO_6WlH06m0?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>Details of the DirtySixer AllRoad Mark II are thin on the ground. What we do know is that this 36″ wheel bicycle will be available in sizes XL-5XL accomodating riders <em>from</em> 5’8″ up to 7′ 6″ and beyond. The new bike is due to have an RRP of $4,999 USD but will be available to pre-order over the coming weeks for just $3,000 USD.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064756/dirtysixer-36-inch-wheel-commuter-bike-all-road-mark-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064756/dirtysixer-36-inch-wheel-commuter-bike-all-road-mark-2.jpg\" alt=\"dirtysixer 36er all-road commuter bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064756/dirtysixer-36-inch-wheel-commuter-bike-all-road-mark-2.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064756/dirtysixer-36-inch-wheel-commuter-bike-all-road-mark-2-297x223.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064756/dirtysixer-36-inch-wheel-commuter-bike-all-road-mark-2-800x600.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064756/dirtysixer-36-inch-wheel-commuter-bike-all-road-mark-2-120x90.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01064756/dirtysixer-36-inch-wheel-commuter-bike-all-road-mark-2-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>The DirtySixer AllRoad Mark II will comprise a 6061 aluminium frame paired with a chromoly steel rigid fork. The new model gets lighter tubeless-ready 36″ rims, 2-piston hydraulic disc brakes with 203mm rotors front and rear, as well as custom-designed extra large pedals, grips, and custom 2-piece cranks (up to 200mm long on the 5XL). Aside from the lower standover, geometry remains unchanged.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01074503/dirtysixer-all-road-mark-II-sizing-XL-5XL.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01074503/dirtysixer-all-road-mark-II-sizing-XL-5XL.jpg\" alt=\"DIRTY SIXER SIXING CHART XL-5XL ALL-ROAD MARK 2\" width=\"1600\" height=\"542\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01074503/dirtysixer-all-road-mark-II-sizing-XL-5XL.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01074503/dirtysixer-all-road-mark-II-sizing-XL-5XL-297x101.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01074503/dirtysixer-all-road-mark-II-sizing-XL-5XL-800x271.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01074503/dirtysixer-all-road-mark-II-sizing-XL-5XL-120x41.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01074503/dirtysixer-all-road-mark-II-sizing-XL-5XL-768x260.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/01074503/dirtysixer-all-road-mark-II-sizing-XL-5XL-1536x520.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/01/29/aasq-103-why-would-you-want-a-wheel-size-larger-than-29/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">36er bikes aren’t new</a>, of course. David Folch (6’6″), the owner of DirtySixer, has been building 36″ wheel bikes for many years. A crash while riding a bike that was too small for him prompted his creation of the DirtySixer brand. David also builds a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2017/03/15/nahbs-2017-dirtysixers-32-road-road-bikes-head-kickstarter/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">32er</a> for folk who are too tall for a bike with regular 29″ wheels, but too short to ride the 36er, though these haven’t made it to production yet.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.dirtysixer.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>DirtySixer.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"a4141bf9586b5a81ec22a797c4bebf37706e1c9d85450311d2a83a8cb7a95f8d","category":"Cycling"}